cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.DS

This paper focuses on enhancing the performance of deep neural networks by incorporating domain knowledge, specifically monotonic trends. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary focus of the paper. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel loss function for enforcing partial monotonicity, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of deep neural networks for image classification, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Furthermore, the paper discusses the importance of preserving the flexibility of deep networks, which is related to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses metrics such as AUC and monotonicity, which are related to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
